WEBVTT

00:01.936 --> 00:04.370
Okay, so it's day two
and your sister-in-law

00:04.372 --> 00:07.539
was cat-sitting your 23-year-old
diabetic short-haired tabby

00:07.541 --> 00:08.774
named noonie.

00:08.776 --> 00:10.376
So you stayed the night
in a hotel,

00:10.378 --> 00:12.211
and that's when you finally told
your wife that you got fired.

00:12.213 --> 00:14.046
But she was too high
to remember it?

00:14.048 --> 00:16.482
Is that why I'm here?
Weed gummies?

00:16.484 --> 00:19.051
You were smuggling a product
that you stole

00:19.053 --> 00:20.986
from your former company,

00:20.988 --> 00:23.322
and you left it in the trunk
of your minivan

00:23.324 --> 00:24.356
with this mechanic.

00:24.358 --> 00:25.891
Okay, I didn't just
leave it there.

00:25.893 --> 00:28.060
I hid it very well, thank you.
Where?

00:28.062 --> 00:30.162
In those little side panels
in the trunk?

00:30.164 --> 00:32.498
That's where<i> everyone</i>
hides stuff.

00:32.500 --> 00:35.300
You're a real dummy,
aren't you, Mr. Parker?

00:35.302 --> 00:37.469
Did you need me to
answer that?

00:37.471 --> 00:40.572
♪♪

00:51.852 --> 00:54.153
Hey, boss.
Just stepping out for a bit.

00:54.155 --> 00:56.522
Okay.
10, 15 minutes tops.

00:56.524 --> 00:59.391
Yep, that's fine.
Yeah, just gonna go to lunch.

00:59.393 --> 01:02.194
I know it's early, but, uh,
i skipped breakfast

01:02.196 --> 01:04.296
and I am as hungry
as a...

01:04.298 --> 01:06.765
[ Inhales deeply ] Lion.

01:06.767 --> 01:08.033
A lion?

01:08.035 --> 01:10.169
No. I'm not lying.
It's all true.

01:10.171 --> 01:12.337
That shawarma place
I'm going to down the road,

01:12.339 --> 01:14.773
I got a reservation, everything.
You can call them.

01:14.775 --> 01:16.175
I'll -- I'll definitely
be there.

01:16.177 --> 01:17.876
I just want to keep you
looped in.

01:17.878 --> 01:19.511
You know, synergy,
'cause I'm...

01:19.513 --> 01:22.147
Going for a walk...
Alone.

01:22.149 --> 01:23.882
So no lunch?

01:23.884 --> 01:26.418
No. Unless...No.

01:28.289 --> 01:30.389
Okay.
Yeah.

01:31.659 --> 01:33.392
[ Motor whirring ]

01:33.394 --> 01:35.727
[ Whirring stops ]
Hey!

01:35.729 --> 01:37.663
Are you Nate Parker?

01:37.665 --> 01:38.897
Yes! Yeah, come here.
What?!

01:38.899 --> 01:40.699
Shh. I can't hear you
over the scooter.

01:40.701 --> 01:42.034
Just stop -- stop yelling.

01:42.036 --> 01:43.802
Are you Nate Parker?
Yes. Come on.

01:43.804 --> 01:45.671
One second.
Just give me a second.

01:45.673 --> 01:47.005
So you said you got
a story for me?

01:47.007 --> 01:49.241
Yeah. It's all right here.
What's this?

01:49.243 --> 01:50.876
This, my friend,
is your pulitzer.

01:50.878 --> 01:52.678
My what?
[ Scoffs ]

01:52.680 --> 01:55.881
I work for a good company
that's just doing a bad thing,

01:55.883 --> 01:58.383
and I need you to shine
a light on that.

01:58.385 --> 01:59.518
Okay. That's cool, man.

01:59.520 --> 02:01.453
Just -- you wanna write that up,
e-mail it to me?

02:01.455 --> 02:03.021
N-no, that's your job.

02:03.023 --> 02:04.590
You're -- you're the journalist.
I'm just the source, okay?

02:04.592 --> 02:06.291
The story's all here.

02:06.293 --> 02:08.961
You just gotta frame it and print it.
But we're online only.

02:08.963 --> 02:10.629
There's no "print."
[ Blows raspberry ]

02:10.631 --> 02:12.297
Excuse me. Can I park there?

02:12.299 --> 02:14.299
Uh, no, we're --
we're saving this spot.

02:14.301 --> 02:15.634
You can't save spots.

02:15.636 --> 02:17.336
Yes, we can. Okay? And there's
plenty of other spots.

02:17.338 --> 02:19.705
There's one right there.
Don't look at me like that.

02:19.707 --> 02:21.306
Look over there.

02:21.308 --> 02:23.208
[ Singsongy ] Thank you.
[ Engine revs, tires squeal ]

02:23.210 --> 02:26.778
Listen, dude, this all seems
like a lot of work, okay?

02:26.780 --> 02:29.148
I usually just reblog stuff
from the ap.

02:29.150 --> 02:31.650
What ap? [ Chuckles ]
Bro, you're so old.

02:31.652 --> 02:33.819
It's, like, this thing that
they have now that just, like,

02:33.821 --> 02:36.522
blasts out all the news
from everywhere.

02:36.524 --> 02:38.123
You're talking about the A.P.?
The Associated Press?

02:38.125 --> 02:40.225
Yeah, it's like "Rooters."
It's dope.

02:40.227 --> 02:42.227
You mean Reuters?
No, Rooters.

02:42.229 --> 02:44.863
No, Reuters.
Oh, is that how you say it?

02:44.865 --> 02:46.465
Yes.
I'm such a dumbass.

02:46.467 --> 02:49.001
Listen, I have risked everything
to bring this to you.

02:49.003 --> 02:51.003
And trust me, you were not
my first choice.

02:51.005 --> 02:53.906
Oh, why would I be? Do you want to be
a dumbass for the rest of your life

02:53.908 --> 02:55.374
and reblog shit
other people wrote,

02:55.376 --> 02:57.176
or do you want to be
a real journalist?

02:57.178 --> 02:59.211
Okay, and break stories
and potentially save

02:59.213 --> 03:01.113
millions of lives
in the process?

03:01.115 --> 03:04.116
He wasn't leaving that spot.
He was adjusting his park job.

03:04.118 --> 03:06.351
He was all crooked.
Then go park on the roof.

03:06.353 --> 03:09.621
I can't. My leather seats get
too hot, and I'm wearing shorts.

03:09.623 --> 03:12.024
Okay. So what's the product?

03:12.026 --> 03:15.427
This is --
[ Horn blares ]

03:15.429 --> 03:18.130
It's... [ mouths words ]
[ Horn blares ]

03:18.132 --> 03:20.632
It's --
[ Horn blares ]

03:20.634 --> 03:22.134
Oh, my gosh. Shut up!

03:22.136 --> 03:23.769
Whoa.
I trust you. I trust you.

03:23.771 --> 03:25.837
[ Horn blaring ]

03:25.839 --> 03:28.340
Man: ♪ somewhere behind
the mountains ♪

03:28.342 --> 03:31.310
♪ there is a place
i figured out... ♪

03:31.312 --> 03:33.712
[ Music warps, rewinds ]

03:33.714 --> 03:35.847
[ Whirring sound ]

03:35.849 --> 03:39.184
♪♪

03:42.823 --> 03:44.223
Jared: I'm so thirsty.

03:44.225 --> 03:46.124
Robin: You just finished
my entire bottle of water.

03:46.126 --> 03:47.693
Nate: Hey, can you get
the bags for me?

03:47.695 --> 03:49.995
Delilah:
I could use a drink, too.

03:49.997 --> 03:52.731
Oh, my god. You are the most
overhydrated generation.

03:52.733 --> 03:54.299
Where is this guy?

03:54.301 --> 03:55.968
Can I have some of your juice?
Nope. Mommy's juice.

03:55.970 --> 03:57.636
It's alcohol.
Mnh-mnh.

03:57.638 --> 03:58.837
No, it's a Mimosa.

03:58.839 --> 04:00.806
Delilah: Doesn't that have alcohol?
Shh.

04:00.808 --> 04:02.608
Can I try some?
No. It's not for kids.

04:02.610 --> 04:03.942
Just give him a sip.
What?

04:03.944 --> 04:05.477
What? You drank
when you were his age.

04:05.479 --> 04:06.778
No, I was way older.

04:06.780 --> 04:09.648
No, you were way...12.
What if he likes it?

04:09.650 --> 04:11.750
What do you think of carrots?
Too spicy.

04:11.752 --> 04:13.018
He's not gonna like it.
All right.

04:13.020 --> 04:15.821
Here.
You're welcome.

04:15.823 --> 04:17.856
[ Whispering ] No.

04:18.993 --> 04:21.059
No.

04:21.996 --> 04:24.463
No.
[ Door opens ]

04:24.465 --> 04:26.865
Oh, door's open. Let's go.
Too late. Lost your chance.

04:26.867 --> 04:29.034
Go, go, go. Go, go, go.
Go, go. What? What?

04:29.036 --> 04:30.469
Davey?

04:30.471 --> 04:32.371
Davey?

04:32.373 --> 04:34.539
Davey!

04:34.541 --> 04:36.675
Dave?
There he is.

04:36.677 --> 04:38.510
Oh, yeah.

04:38.512 --> 04:39.845
[ Clears throat ] Davey?

04:39.847 --> 04:42.648
Hey, Davey?
Hey, it's Nate Parker.

04:42.650 --> 04:45.951
Uh, I'm here to pick up
the car you're sleeping in.

04:45.953 --> 04:48.487
Is he dead?

04:48.489 --> 04:50.889
Davey?
[ Door squeaks ]

04:50.891 --> 04:52.791
Oh, my god.
Oh, it smells like it.

04:52.793 --> 04:54.359
Give him a poke.

04:54.361 --> 04:57.162
Davey? Dave?

04:57.164 --> 04:58.497
[ Snores ]

04:58.499 --> 05:00.599
He's -- he's alive.

05:00.601 --> 05:03.602
Dave? Davey? Davey?

05:03.604 --> 05:05.771
Davey? Davey! Davey!

05:05.773 --> 05:08.440
Davey! Davey! Davey! Davey! Davey!
Nate. Nate. Nate. Nate!

05:08.442 --> 05:11.443
Please stop yelling!
It's like a jackhammer in here.

05:11.445 --> 05:12.778
Oh, I'm sorry, potsie.

05:12.780 --> 05:14.446
Do you have a better idea
how to wake him up?

05:14.448 --> 05:16.648
[ Metal clanging loudly ]

05:16.650 --> 05:18.183
Stop it!
[ Clanging stops ]

05:18.185 --> 05:21.119
What's wrong with him?
He's drunk.

05:21.121 --> 05:23.288
Oh, no, he's not drunk.
He drank some poison water.

05:23.290 --> 05:24.323
That's probably alcohol,

05:24.325 --> 05:25.991
but yes, technically,
it is poison.

05:25.993 --> 05:27.459
Probably tastes awful!

05:27.461 --> 05:30.028
It does. Well, you gotta
train yourself to like it.

05:30.030 --> 05:31.363
Yeah, and if you do,
you end up like that guy.

05:31.365 --> 05:33.031
No. That's not what happens
when you drink.

05:33.033 --> 05:34.633
What are you doing?
I had them scared straight.

05:34.635 --> 05:36.501
Why would you walk that back in?
Because it's not true.

05:36.503 --> 05:39.604
Most people just drink
to have fun and socialize.

05:39.606 --> 05:41.540
I socialize.
I always have fun.

05:41.542 --> 05:43.675
Wait. If I drink,
i have more fun?!

05:43.677 --> 05:45.210
No. You're kids.
You don't drink.

05:45.212 --> 05:47.045
So why do<i> you</i> drink?
I don't.

05:47.047 --> 05:48.347
You're drinking right now.

05:48.349 --> 05:50.148
I'm bringing myself
back up to zero.

05:50.150 --> 05:51.383
Okay, listen, people drink
for a multitude

05:51.385 --> 05:53.185
of different reasons.
[ Sighs deeply ]

05:53.187 --> 05:54.953
Sometimes you have a hard
day at work... Mm-hmm.

05:54.955 --> 05:57.356
And you need to unwind.
She doesn't work.

05:57.358 --> 05:59.024
Excuse me. What do you call
raising the two of you?

05:59.026 --> 06:00.292
We go to school all day.

06:00.294 --> 06:01.927
Do you drink while
we're in school?

06:01.929 --> 06:03.595
No. If you were in school
all the time,

06:03.597 --> 06:05.397
I wouldn't<i> need</i> to drink.
Did you say you "need" to drink?

06:05.399 --> 06:07.466
I -- no.
I'm saying that sometimes,

06:07.468 --> 06:09.735
for instance,
after conversations like this,

06:09.737 --> 06:11.470
I just need
to loosen up a bit.

06:11.472 --> 06:12.771
I thought that's why
you do yoga.

06:12.773 --> 06:15.006
<i> Okay,</i> what I'm saying is,

06:15.008 --> 06:17.943
don't do what I do or you're
gonna end up like that guy.

06:17.945 --> 06:19.611
[ Wheezes ] [ Gasps
loudly ] Oh, my god.

06:19.613 --> 06:21.947
Oh, jeez. Somebody help me.
I got it.

06:21.949 --> 06:24.316
[ Strained voice ] Oh, my god.
You're so dense.

06:24.318 --> 06:25.917
[ Groaning ]

06:25.919 --> 06:27.786
<i> Oh,</i> my god.

06:27.788 --> 06:29.287
I don't know what to do.
Oh, my god!

06:29.289 --> 06:30.856
Aah!
Oh, shit!

06:30.858 --> 06:32.924
[ Gurgling ]

06:32.926 --> 06:35.527
Nate: $108. I don't see
how that adds up. Ahh.

06:35.529 --> 06:37.295
$80 for this?
Sorry, folks.

06:37.297 --> 06:39.498
That's what happens when
you don't drink enough water.

06:39.500 --> 06:42.801
Kids,
you gotta stay hydrated.

06:42.803 --> 06:45.036
Great. So, uh,
we're good to go?

06:45.038 --> 06:47.305
Oh, yeah.
She's as good as new.

06:47.307 --> 06:48.774
You sure about that?
[ Rattling ]

06:48.776 --> 06:50.308
Oh, yeah. Yeah.
What?

06:50.310 --> 06:53.945
No, you gotta give it
one of these.

06:53.947 --> 06:56.047
Ahh.
Jesus.

06:56.049 --> 06:57.983
Simple enough. There you go.
Ooh.

06:57.985 --> 07:00.552
[ Inhales deeply ]
That's your solution, huh?

07:00.554 --> 07:02.421
Give it a fonzie?
A what?

07:02.423 --> 07:05.257
A fonzie. The -- the fonz.
You just did it.

07:05.259 --> 07:06.758
[ As Henry winkler's fonzie ]
Eyyy.

07:06.760 --> 07:08.093
I never said, "eyyy,"

07:08.095 --> 07:11.196
but I did upgrade
your side door.

07:13.801 --> 07:15.100
[ Grunts ]

07:15.102 --> 07:16.768
[ Door squeaking and grinding
loudly ]

07:16.770 --> 07:18.403
[ Sniffs ]

07:18.405 --> 07:20.305
[ Metal scraping ]
Eyyy.

07:20.307 --> 07:21.807
Wow. That is...

07:21.809 --> 07:23.275
[ Knocks on door ]
Bang-up job.

07:23.277 --> 07:25.911
Hey, what is this?
Oh, yeah. About that.

07:25.913 --> 07:28.346
I ran the V.I.N.,
and a D.U.I. Popped up.

07:28.348 --> 07:30.582
So I had to glue one of those
bad boys on your starter.

07:30.584 --> 07:32.651
That's probably a mistake.

07:32.653 --> 07:34.186
No, that is a mistake.
Run it again.

07:34.188 --> 07:36.154
Yeah, I ran it a few times
on account of you folks

07:36.156 --> 07:38.757
don't seem like the type,
but V.I.N. Don't lie.

07:38.759 --> 07:42.027
Well, clearly it does, because
we don't drink and drive.

07:42.029 --> 07:43.695
Yeah, everyone says that.

07:43.697 --> 07:45.130
No, I know that,

07:45.132 --> 07:47.466
but<i> we</i> really don't
drink and drive, so...

07:47.468 --> 07:49.634
Yeah, everybody says that, too.

07:49.636 --> 07:51.970
Nate, let's just go.
No, no, no.

07:51.972 --> 07:53.805
Take it off.
I can't.

07:53.807 --> 07:56.708
[ Tab pops ]
We're a zero tolerance county.

07:56.710 --> 07:59.644
[ Gulping ]

07:59.646 --> 08:02.147
[ Blows air ]
This is broken.

08:02.149 --> 08:05.083
It's not working. [ Exhales
] You gotta hum into it.

08:05.085 --> 08:06.918
[ Hums ]

08:06.920 --> 08:09.921
It's so alcoholics like you
can't cheat the system.

08:09.923 --> 08:12.390
[ Humming ]
Listen to me,

08:12.392 --> 08:14.826
I have never,
ever operated a vehicle

08:14.828 --> 08:16.394
under the influence.

08:16.396 --> 08:19.564
Yeah, well, you'll certainly
never do it again, will ya?

08:19.566 --> 08:22.667
[ Continues humming ]

08:22.669 --> 08:27.572
[ Breathalyzer beeping ] Automated
female voice: <i> Fail. Fail. Fail.</i>

08:27.574 --> 08:30.842
♪♪

08:32.079 --> 08:34.579
[ Sniffing ]

08:34.581 --> 08:38.517
Are you guys alcoholics?
No. That was a computer glitch.

08:38.519 --> 08:41.253
So why didn't you tell that guy
to take this thing off?

08:41.255 --> 08:43.121
I did. Why don't you ask
your mother

08:43.123 --> 08:45.023
why she insisted we keep it?
Because the guy wasn't listening.

08:45.025 --> 08:46.324
It would've taken too long.

08:46.326 --> 08:47.959
And we wanna get
to the beach, right?

08:47.961 --> 08:50.695
Why is it so hot in here?
Is this not on?

08:50.697 --> 08:52.597
[ Explosion ]
Aah! Oh!

08:52.599 --> 08:54.032
[ Tires squeal ]

08:54.034 --> 08:56.968
That man's drunk.
[ Loud crash ]

08:56.970 --> 08:59.104
[ Tires squealing ]

08:59.106 --> 09:01.406
[ Coughs ] Give me a drink!
Here. Here.

09:01.408 --> 09:03.241
[ Coughs ]

09:03.243 --> 09:04.576
Aah! Aah!

09:04.578 --> 09:07.646
Why would you give me alcohol?!
You seem tense!

09:07.648 --> 09:09.714
[ Coughing ]
Ooh.

09:09.716 --> 09:10.982
[ Breathalyzer beeping ]
Why is that beeping now?

09:10.984 --> 09:12.817
It says it's a random
running retest.

09:12.819 --> 09:15.554
I already blew in it!
[ Humming ]

09:15.556 --> 09:18.823
Automated female voice: <i> Fail. Fail. Fail.</i>
You failed 'cause you're drunk.

09:18.825 --> 09:21.393
It says here some models
may honk repeatedly.

09:21.395 --> 09:24.329
[ Horn honking ]
Aah!

09:24.331 --> 09:25.730
Davey!

09:25.732 --> 09:27.599
[ Beeping and honking continue ]

09:27.601 --> 09:29.100
Somebody look up
how to cheat this thing.

09:29.102 --> 09:31.102
[ Touchscreens clicking ]
Oh, oh, oh!

09:31.104 --> 09:32.337
Pennies! Pennies!
Pennies work.

09:32.339 --> 09:33.838
No, no, no.
That's an urban legend.

09:33.840 --> 09:35.740
No, no, no, copper
neutralizes the alcohol.

09:35.742 --> 09:37.242
That's so gross --
it's so gross.

09:37.244 --> 09:39.477
[ Muffled voice ]
Do you have a better idea?!

09:39.479 --> 09:40.912
[ Humming ]

09:40.914 --> 09:43.615
Ooh! Do we have
a 12-volt mattress inflater?

09:43.617 --> 09:45.750
I don't know. Do we? Do we?
Look in the back! No! No!

09:45.752 --> 09:47.852
[ Humming ] Oh, here's a way
to beat a breathalyzer.

09:47.854 --> 09:49.354
What?! What is it?!
Don't drink.

09:49.356 --> 09:52.190
<i> Fail. Fail.</i>
Give me that thing.

09:52.192 --> 09:54.693
[ Humming ] You know, you
could've helped, you know.

09:54.695 --> 09:56.261
I'm -- I'm more drunk
than anyone else --

09:56.263 --> 09:58.129
I know that!
That's the problem!

09:58.131 --> 09:59.798
[ Continues humming ]
[ Siren wailing ]

09:59.800 --> 10:01.600
♪♪

10:01.602 --> 10:03.868
[ Siren continues wailing ]

10:03.870 --> 10:05.637
Oh, shit.
[ Continues humming ]

10:05.639 --> 10:08.473
[ Spitting ]

10:08.475 --> 10:09.808
Mnh.

10:09.810 --> 10:11.977
[ Spits ]

10:11.979 --> 10:13.478
[ Knob clicks, explosion ]

10:13.480 --> 10:15.780
[ Coughing ]

10:19.186 --> 10:23.655
Hmm. I just used one of these,
and now I can't remember.

10:23.657 --> 10:27.225
I'm pretty sure
this one's the freshie.

10:27.227 --> 10:29.194
Wait, you're<i> pretty</i> sure?
Mostly sure.

10:29.196 --> 10:30.829
Yeah, you're gonna get
some alcohol first or...

10:30.831 --> 10:33.131
You<i> would</i> like that,
you drunk.

10:33.133 --> 10:35.333
Excuse me, sir, um,
is this really necessary?

10:35.335 --> 10:38.236
You refused the breathalyzer.
Yeah, because I'm not drunk.

10:38.238 --> 10:39.404
Hold still.

10:39.406 --> 10:41.573
Yeah, I would like to request
the same of you.

10:41.575 --> 10:43.908
Look, sir, do -- do you know
the mechanic, Davey, up the way?

10:43.910 --> 10:45.176
This is all his fault.

10:45.178 --> 10:47.379
Davey? From Davey Wheels
and Tires?

10:47.381 --> 10:49.848
That place burned down
20 years ago.

10:49.850 --> 10:52.717
Davey was in there that night.
Burned to death.

10:52.719 --> 10:56.388
You're thinking Gary.
Gary's Tires and Wheels, Arnie.

10:56.390 --> 10:57.922
Right. I'm sorry.

10:57.924 --> 10:59.190
Gary burned to death.

10:59.192 --> 11:00.859
Ow!
I said hold still.

11:00.861 --> 11:02.994
Now you made me miss
the vein.

11:02.996 --> 11:04.462
What -- ow! Don't twist it!

11:04.464 --> 11:06.498
God! You put an air bubble
in there, you'll kill me.

11:06.500 --> 11:09.134
Is that right? That'd be
even worse way to die.

11:09.136 --> 11:11.202
